There was a person who in charge of the fish department standing by the customer service desk. I told him the fish stinky situation and his answer was ‚ÄúTHAT‚ÄôS IT!‚Äù Then I  asked the woman at the customers services desk next to him.  She looked at the man and she refused to refund me.  After the arguments, then she asked me where was the smelt?  I am keeping it cooked in the freezer home including the original bag which the price stickers still on for the evidence.  Well, I live in Malden but shopping in Boston.  Not convenient to Boston that often.  I have been living in Massachusetts for 30 years.  This Ming supermarket had changed owners many times.  The owner or shares holders mostly came from the countryside of China. They don‚Äôt have knowledges to keep the food at the low temperature safe.  They never put the expiration date on the fish or vegetable such as yellow leek $9.99 a pound.  They are trying to sell everything as long as they can.  They mixed the new items and old items to sell.  For example, the steamers were at least a quarter dead and stinky.  You can see the bad dead steamers is floating in the water . The good steamers is sinking in the water.  That is how the consumers get sick or get poisoning so easily after consuming the unsafe food.  Our livers got damaged too.  Never choose New Ming Supermarket!  Go C-Mart fresh food.", 'time': 1652855076}]
